## 2. Container-level notes

* Standard DBPF 1.0 exactly as already handled by `addons/dbpf/DBPF.gd`; the engine's QFS
  decompressor and DIR handling load every subfile in this save without error.
* Almost every savegame subfile lives in group `0x299B2D1B` (121 of 179 entries). The
  exceptions: LTEXTs (`0x6AAEE931/32` name/mayor, `0x4A2482BB` thumbnail labels), PNG
  thumbnails (`0x4A2482BB`), terrain (`0xE98F9525`), the region-view record (`0xCA027EE1`)
  and a handful of singletons.
* Savegame records follow SC4's standard serialization: `u32 size, u32 CRC, u32 memory
  address`, then a version and class-specific payload. 120 of the 133 types chain
  cleanly as size-prefixed record arrays (verified while counting the records above).
* Two well-known network subfiles are **absent** — Network subfile 2 (`0xCA16374F`,
  bridges/elevated) and the tunnel subfile (`0x8A4BD52F`) — consistent with a flat tutorial
  city that has no bridges or tunnels.

## 3. Implementation status in OpenSC4 (summary)

**Implemented today (10 of the 133 types present, ≈49% of the decompressed bytes):**
building/prop/flora occupants, lots, lot base textures, terrain altitudes (main map only),
region-view stats, PNG thumbnails, LTEXT, and the DIR directory. In short: **everything the
current city renderer needs, and nothing of the simulation.**

**Not implemented (present in this save):** all network subfiles, the item index, zone
developer/manager, tract developer, all 136 SimGrid layers, every simulator/manager state
blob, budget (departments, line items, taxes), the ~20 ordinances, historical graph data,
advice state, and the COM-serializer registry.

**Engine scaffolding waiting on this data:** `CityView/ClassDefinitions/` (NetGraphNode,
NetGraphEdge, NetTile, TransitTile) models a transit-network graph but no parser feeds it —
the network subfiles in §4.4 are exactly the missing input.

Also worth noting: the region UI derives the displayed city name from the *filename*
(`RegionCityView.gd:22`), while the save carries properly localized name/mayor LTEXTs.

